main event: A witness in New Carlisle, Ohio reported seeing two unidentified objects in the sky on December 5, 1955.
interesting points: The objects displayed 'erratic' motion, flying for 20 minutes.
The witness had previously reported seeing a similar object on March 16, 1965.
The objects were described as reddish in color, with a low humming sound.
The witness was asked to provide a sketch showing the objects' path and elevation above the horizon.
The objects were observed during the day, with a clear sky and no clouds.
